beer_description: Our Hop Knot IPA is made only from American malt and lots of American hops, which produce a big, broad-shouldered, hoppy beer backed up by a character as warm as, well, Mom and apple pie? Hop Knot IPA get its peculiar name from the weaving of five different hops added at seven different times during the brewing process. Including our cavernous hop-back, which gets so stuffed with whole leaf hops that we feel genuine guilt for its excess. Hop Knot is an ale that is to be enjoyed with friends, spicy food or any time you need a good hop fix without the harsh bitterness. We hope you enjoy this pioneering beer made in the bold spirit of Americans everywhere.

The fruity aroma and hoppy, spicy flavor makes Troubadour Blond very easy drinkable and extremely refreshing. The full malty and slightly spicy body is followed by a mild bitter aftertaste. This with just the 4 basic ingredients of beer: water, malt, hops and yeast!
Bourbon Black Cherry Porter is Bourbon barrel aged for 9 months. This porter is brewed with sweet black cherries.

Five brewers went "all in" to form Full Pint Brewing Company. Our first collaborative brew, All In Amber, combines a select variety of English and German malts balanced nicely by our signature American hop addition.

Hops: Warrior, Fuggle.
Malts: Maris Otter, Pale, Crystal, Munich, Brown, Chocolate

This beer is ?The One? Dick?s brew crew is most proud of.

Brewed in honor of our mentor and friend, Dick Young, we hope you knock a few back in his honor and memory. Dick loved his Danger Ale, so we thought it was fitting that we use his original recipe and make it a bit more dangerous. The Double Danger?s smooth flavor makes this beer a highly drinkable ale.

This beer doesn?t fit any category, won?t fit into some set criteria ? and we like it that way.

beer_description: An American amber ale with a Northwest twist: generous amounts of Amarillo and Glacier hops give this beer its big fruity and citrusy flavor as well as its bitter, lasting finish.
Out of Bounds stout with a half-pound of fresh Malawi coffee generously donated by The Unseen Bean, whose roastery is just around the corner.
A double chocolate oatmeal milk imperial stout served on Nitrogen

Quintessential American style Imperial/ Double I.P.A. Deep golden in color, it is both bold and balanced. 
2008 & 2009 GABF medalist.

The Popol Vuh, the sacred book of the Maya, unfolds a complex web of mystery around a beverage known as xocoatl (ch-co-atle). At Southern Tier, we're not surprised that hieroglyphs of the ancient Maya depict chocolate being poured for rulers and gods. Even through the many voyages of Columbus, the mystical bean remained nothing more than a strange currency of the native peoples.

Moving through centuries, the circular journey of cacao has been realized in our brewing house, encompassing the complexity of the darkest, bitter-sweet candy together with the original frothy cold beverage of the ancient Maya to bring to you our Blackwater Series Choklat Stout. We have combined the finest ingredients to tempt your senses & renew the power & interrelation of history in every bottle.

2-row barley / caramel 60 malt / barley flakes / chocolate malt / bittersweet Belgian chocolate / kettle hops: chinook & willamette
A pretty okay Homebrew. Reminds me of Deschutes Mirror Pond Pale Ale a bit.
A winter favorite with a great blend of flavors. Best served at near room temp!
Rye IPA

beer_description: Our Pilsner is a Northern German style hopped with German Tettnanger hops and has garnered 7 medals so far including Jeffco County Fair, Colorado State Fair and the All-Colorado Beerfest and Competition (took 1st overall in Lagers!), as well as 2nd place in a national competition called Best of Craft. Third Place winner at 2011 Colorado State Fair.
Coffee and light sweetness, creamy with lingering slightly burnt malt finish
From Ed Wort's recipe.

An Autumn ale that captures the essence of the harvest season. Fresh whole ginger, cinnamon, all spice and nutmeg give this pumpkin ale its distinctive character,
without any syrupy sweetness.

Brewed with fresh harvested spring honey, stolen from some very angry bees (we have the welts to prove it) and infused with our own special painstakingly, handpicked blueberry essence. A light refreshing ale with a nice blueberry aroma, crackery malt flavors with a hint of sweetness and a light tart blueberry finish. "Most Refreshing Beer in America" 1st Place - Brewing News Global Warming Open

An extra strong stout weighing in at 6% abv, brewed by Carlow Brewing Company in 2008 to celebrate 10 years of brewing.  
Chocolate and coffee flavours mingle in this silky smooth stout and linger on the pallet balanced with the spicy hoppy bitterness. 
This brew matches well with strong cheeses or cured meats

Hoss is based on the M?rzen lagers of Germany. Rich, layered malt notes, with hints of cherry and dark fruits, dominate, while the unique addition of rye imparts a slightly earthy, spicy character. Hoss finishes crisp and dry, and its brilliant red-orange color is a toast to the sunsets that make the perfect backdrop for this beer.
100% Centennial whole hops.
On a cork tap - ~6% abv

Imperial stout was originally brewed to satisfy the Czarist courts. Because it was transported across the freezing Baltic, Russian imperial stout was brewed with a high level of alcohol. Rich, flavorful, deep chocolate color, with a roasted barley nose. Break down that wall... or conform & be dull.

beer_description:
Abita S.O.S.? (Save Our Shore) ? a charitable pilsner is a message in a bottle...a distress signal for the troubled waters of our Gulf Coast. For every bottle sold Abita donates 75? to the rescue and restoration of the environment, industry and individuals fighting to survive the disastrous gulf oil spill. This unfiltered Weizen Pils is made with pilsner and wheat malts. It is hopped and dry hopped with Sterling and German Perle hops. It has a brilliant gold color, a sweet malt flavor, and a pleasant bitterness and aroma.

In addition, related retail merchandise (hats, t-shirts, lapel pins, decals and car magnets) are sold and 100% of the net proceeds go to the SOS Fund.
Barrel blend of porter, nut brown aged on rasperrys!

beer_description: A chocolate american dry stout.

The Loving Cup, although boasting a complex malt profile of 7 different grains, is a classic brown porter at heart. Pure Vermont grade A maple syrup is added at the end of the boil to lend a subtle sweetness and maple aromatics. The maple is balanced out by roasty British chocolate malts, making this seasonal ale highly drinkable and the perfect treat for any time of year. For maximum enjoyment, pair with chilly nights and good friends.
A pilsner light and refreshing beer with a balanced finish, and good drinkability.

English style dark ale made with roasted malt and aromatic hop. The bitter flavors reminiscent chocolate and coffee are unforgettable. It is rich, but still refreshing, making it easy to drink.
Bask in the head?s floral bouquet. Relish citrus accents from dry hopping. Sweet, yet balanced, with a finish that never turns too bitter.

beer_description:
A rock 'n roll partnership between Scotland's best new distillery (Distiller of the Year 2007) and Scotland's hardcore new microbrewery (Gold MedalWinner, World Beer Cup 2008).

Paradox, Isle of Arran Edition, see's BrewDog's killer 15% Imperial Stout matured in stunning whisky casks from the Arran distillery.

The rich vanilla sweetness, hints of cinnamon and balancing aromatic fruit and ginger flavours of the Arran Malt are all completely infused  deep into the texture of our smooth, robust, Imperial Stout.

Profund new depths emerge with each pass and sip, the pallet is as pollished and classic as a Robbie Burns masterpiece, this is Scotland in a glass.

Yellow blond, slightly cloudy because of the wheat beer. 

Honey and more in particular Acaia honey, a subtle hint of vanilla. 

Sweet and light bitter, evolving into the rich taste palate of honey.

This is our special ale from the brewers at Anchor. It is sold only from early November to mid-January. The Ale?s recipe is different every year, but the intent with which we offer it remains the same: joy and celebration of the newness of life. Since ancient times, trees have symbolized the winter solstice when the earth, with its seasons appears born anew.
beer_name: Merry Christmas & Happy New Year (Our Special Ale) (2010)

beer_description:
An unfiltered wheat beer in the style of those from Bavaria.

A unique yeast strain gives our Hefe-Weizen an aroma of bubblegum, banana and cloves.
Very refreshing and a good choice for a hot Sunshine Coast day.

An oak-aged, gentle giant which has been gaining popularity over the past few years and is now available year-round. Two "threads," or batches, of beer ? an English-style old ale and an imperial IPA ? are brewed and, after separate fermentation in stainless tanks, are transferred and blended together in large oak tanks. Burton Baton sits on the wood for about a month.

When enjoying the Burton Baton, you'll find an awesome blend of the citrus notes from Northwestern hops melding with woody, vanilla notes from the oak.

Mornington Pale is an American-style pale ale, pouring a cloudy golden yellow with a tightly packed white head. Our Pale has both citrus and passion fruit aromas, showcasing American hops added late in the brewing process. A light smooth palate, aided by the generous addition of wheat malts, moderate bitterness and carbonation make for a flavoursome and sessional ale.
Excitable brew, bursting from the bottle
